Actually, sometimes type conversion make some code become a little bit handy.<p>We use Java at the backend and of course Javascript for frontend. When serializing, in Java we should<p><pre><code>        String dataRaw = &quot;42&quot;;
        int objectId = Integer.parseInt(dataRaw);
</code></pre>
Meanwhile, in JS, it is fairly simple:<p><pre><code>        dataRaw = &quot;42&quot;;
        var objectid = +dataRaw;</code></pre>
